    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: I would like to add to Betsy Wade's article "Hotel Penalties for Cancellation," (Practical Traveler, May 12).</p>
        <p>Beware of hotel reservations in Germany: a reservation is a firm booking, not cancelable without a penalty. I got around this in one town, where there is  a Best Western hotel. I booked through Best Western here. It's a pity since I wanted to go native.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: I would like to add to Betsy Wade's article "Hotel Penalties for Cancellation," (Practical Traveler, May 12).</p>
        <p>Beware of hotel reservations in Germany: a reservation is a firm booking, not cancelable without a penalty. I got around this in one town, where there is  a Best Western hotel. I booked through Best Western here. It's a pity since I wanted to go native.</p>
        <p>EVELYN RONELL Secaucus, N.J.</p>
        <p>The German National Tourist Office comments: A minimum charge of one night is customarily imposed if a hotel reservation is canceled in Germany.</p>
      </block>
